during her career she attained several firsts for a woman scientist , including one of the first two women elected a fellow of the royal society ( frs ) in 1945 ( along with marjory stephenson ) , first woman tenured professor at university college london , first woman president of the international union of crystallography , and first woman president of the british association for the advancement of science .

